T1  - Foreign investment quotas and rent extraction under uncertainty
AU  - Bartolini, Leonardo
JO  - Journal of International Economics
VL  - 38
IS  - 1
SP  - 25
EP  - 49
PY  - 1995
DA  - 1995/02/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(94)01332-M
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/002219969401332M
KW  - Quotas
KW  - Foreign direct investment
KW  - Rent runs
AB  - This study examines the effects of quantitative restrictions on foreign firms' entry into a domestic industry. Foreign firms' investment policy and the equilibrium value of their entry right are studied under various rationing and rent-extracting schemes. When foreign firms are left free to compete for the scarcity rents induced by a quota, their policy exhibits a suboptimal ‘rent run’: entry occurs at the optimal pace only until a threshold level of investment is reached; the last group of firms enters early and dumps output at below marginal cost.
