KW  - Liberalization
KW  - Credibility
KW  - Payments deficits
AB  - This paper addresses the question of whether there may be a self-fulfilling aspect to the failure of liberalization attempts when it is widely known the government will abandon the reform if the central bank suffers an unacceptably large loss in reserves. I derive the conditions for both sustained reform and a self-fulfilling failure to be equilibrium outcomes. Under certain well defined conditions, liberalization is most likely to succeed when the capital account is open.
